---
description: Always apply the PM OS workspace operating guide.
alwaysApply: true
---

This project is a PM OS workspace.

Before doing PM work:
- Read @AGENTS.md and @INDEX.md.
- Treat @AGENTS.md as the workspace operating guide, not a duplicate agent profile.
- For PM work, follow @agents/pm-chief.md as the Chief PM coordinator.
- Ground work in @product-docs/product-vision.md.
- Apply @_workspace_setup_docs/skills/apply-pmos-struct.md whenever creating, moving, or editing artifacts.
- Route repeatable workflow or preference changes to @agents/sub-agents/skill-librarian.md.
- When the user provides raw notes or points to a loose notes file, process it automatically:
  create the standard folder, preserve raw input under a `raw/` archive subfolder, write the summary
  in the main folder, remove the loose inbox copy after archiving it, update indexes, and then report
  the created paths. Do not give an option menu in place of filing the notes.
- When the user asks for insights, recommendations, prioritization, MVP scope, trade-offs, or what
  to do next, create an outcome artifact under `product-docs/outcomes/`, update the outcomes index,
  and reply with only a short handoff plus the file path.
- When the user asks about UX, design trade-offs, accessibility, metrics, experiments, roadmaps,
  release planning, exec updates, launch notes, client summaries, or stakeholder alignment, route the
  work through the Chief PM and create the durable artifact under the matching `product-docs/` lane:
  `design/`, `data-insights/`, `roadmaps/`, or `stakeholder-comms/`.

Always keep indexes current:
- Any file or folder created, moved, renamed, or meaningfully edited must update the nearest INDEX.md in the same change.
- If a new top-level area is created, also update the root @INDEX.md.
- Do not leave stale links or undocumented new artifacts.

Keep documentation alive:
- Update @product-docs/product-vision.md when the product, audience, goal, positioning, or strategy changes.
- If another product doc should be updated and the source is clear, route the work through the Chief PM to the right specialist.
- If the PM wants to teach the workspace a new process, route through the Chief PM to the skill-librarian.
- When adding, updating, merging, or removing a skill, also update `product-skills/START_HERE.md`,
  `product-skills/INDEX.md`, `agents/sub-agents/INDEX.md`, the matching sub-agent file, and Chief PM routing.
  Remove orphaned sub-agents or stale skill links in the same change.
- When the PM provides reusable templates or examples for a workflow, put blank formats under
  `product-practices/templates/`, examples/style samples under `product-practices/references/`, update the relevant index,
  and connect the relevant skill to those files.
- Do not overwrite raw notes; create summaries, decisions, PRDs, and documentation as new artifacts.
